6 An Act relating to memorial highway and bridge
designations; designating the Clyde and Grace Cook
7 Memorial Bridge; designating the Terry Walker
Memorial Interchange; designating the Sheriff Marty
8 Grisham Memorial Interchange; designating the MoMM2
Arlon Francis Wetsel Memorial Bridge; designating the
9 John Skelley Memorial Highway; designating the CPT
David Ward Neely Memorial Highway; designating the
10 Patrolman Mark Harris Memorial Interchange;
designating the PV2 Earl Maggart Memorial Bridge;
11 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.510 of Title 69, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 The bridge on U.S. Highway 70 crossing over Winters Creek
19 approximately three (3) miles northeast of Bennington in Bryan
20 County shall be designated as the “Clyde and Grace Cook Memorial
21 Bridge”. The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
22 permanent markers bearing that name to be placed on the bridge.
23
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1966 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.511 of Title 69, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 The interchange of Interstate 35 and Blue Bell Road in Springer,
5 Carter County, shall be designated as the “Terry Walker Memorial
6 Interchange”. The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
7 permanent markers bearing that name to be placed at the interchange.
8 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.512 of Title 69, unless
10 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 The interchange of Interstate 35 and State Highway 32 in
12 Marietta, Love County, shall be designated as the “Sheriff Marty
13 Grisham Memorial Interchange”. The Department of Transportation
14 shall cause suitable permanent markers bearing that name to be
15 placed at the interchange.
16 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.513 of Title 69, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 The bridge on U.S. Highway 283 crossing over Elm Fork Red River
20 north of Mangum in Greer County shall be designated as the “MoMM2
21 Arlon Francis Wetsel Memorial Bridge”. The Department of
22 Transportation shall cause suitable permanent markers bearing that
23 name to be placed on the bridge.
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1966 Page 2

1 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.514 of Title 69, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 The section of State Highway 325 beginning at the intersection
5 of Ellis Avenue in Boise City extending northwesterly to the
6 Oklahoma-New Mexico border in Cimmaron County shall be designated as
7 the “John Skelley Memorial Highway”. The Department of
8 Transportation shall cause suitable permanent markers bearing that
9 name to be placed on the bridge.
10 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.515 of Title 69, unless
12 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 The section of U.S. Highway 169 beginning at the Double Creek
14 Bridge extending south to the county line between Nowata County and
15 Rogers County shall be designated as the “CPT David Ward Neely
16 Memorial Highway”. The Department of Transportation shall cause
17 suitable markers bearing that name to be placed on the highway.
18 SECTION 7. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.516 of Title 69, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 The interchange of Interstate 35 and Flood Avenue in Cleveland
22 County shall be designated as the “Patrolman Mark Harris Memorial
23 Interchange”. The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1966 Page 3

1 perm anent markers bearing that name to be placed at the
2 intersection.
3 SECTION 8. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.517 of Title 69, unless
5 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 The bridge on State Highway 18 about three and one-half (3 1/2)
7 miles south of Pawnee crossing over Camp Creek in Pawnee County
8 shall be designated as the “PV2 Earl Maggart Memorial Bridge”. The
9 Department of Transportation shall cause suitable permanent markers
10 bearing that name to be placed on the bridge.
11 SECTION 9. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
12 Passed the Senate the 25th day of March, 2026.
